#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.28"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.28:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.28:0.2"
msgid "3. Puggalavagga"
msgstr "3. Persons"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.28:0.3"
msgid "28. Gūthabhāṇīsutta"
msgstr "28. Speech like Dung"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.128"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.28:1.1"
msgid "“Tayome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“These three kinds of people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an3.28:1.2"
msgid "Katame tayo?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.28:1.3"
msgid "Gūthabhāṇī, pupphabhāṇī, madhubhāṇī."
msgstr ""
"One with speech like dung, one with speech like flowers, and one with speech "
"like honey."

msgctxt "an3.28:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo gūthabhāṇī?"
msgstr "And who has speech like dung?"

#. VAR: sabhaggato vā → sabhāgoto vā (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: parisaggato vā → parisagato vā (si, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.28:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato "
"vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho "
"purisa, yaṃ jānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti. So ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ vā āha:"
" ‘na jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti; "
"iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who is summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a "
"guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, "
"say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I know.’ Knowing, they say ‘I don’"
"t know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ "
"So they deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for some "
"trivial worldly reason."

msgctxt "an3.28:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo gūthabhāṇī."
msgstr "This is called a person with speech like dung."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.28:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo pupphabhāṇī?"
msgstr "And who has speech like flowers?"

msgctxt "an3.28:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo sabhaggato vā parisaggato vā ñātimajjhagato "
"vā pūgamajjhagato vā rājakulamajjhagato vā abhinīto sakkhipuṭṭho: ‘ehambho "
"purisa, yaṃ pajānāsi taṃ vadehī’ti, so ajānaṃ vā āha: ‘na jānāmī’ti, jānaṃ "
"vā āha: ‘jānāmī’ti, apassaṃ vā āha: ‘na passāmī’ti, passaṃ vā āha: "
"‘passāmī’ti; iti attahetu vā parahetu vā āmisakiñcikkhahetu vā na "
"sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s someone who is summoned to a council, an assembly, a family meeting, a "
"guild, or to the royal court, and asked to bear witness: ‘Please, mister, "
"say what you know.’ Not knowing, they say ‘I don’t know.’ Knowing, they say ‘"
"I know.’ Not seeing, they say ‘I don’t see.’ And seeing, they say ‘I see.’ "
"So they don’t deliberately lie for the sake of themselves or another, or for "
"some trivial worldly reason."

msgctxt "an3.28:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo pupphabhāṇī."
msgstr "This is called a person with speech like flowers."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.28:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, puggalo madhubhāṇī?"
msgstr "And who has speech like honey?"

msgctxt "an3.28:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya "
"paṭivirato hoti;"
msgstr "It’s someone who gives up harsh speech."

msgctxt "an3.28:3.3"
msgid ""
"yā sā vācā nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā "
"bahujanamanāpā tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"They speak in a way that’s mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the "
"heart, polite, likable and agreeable to the people."

msgctxt "an3.28:3.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, puggalo madhubhāṇī."
msgstr "This is called a person with speech like honey."

msgctxt "an3.28:3.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, tayo puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti."
msgstr "These are the three people found in the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.28:3.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
